Odd Future Wolf Gang Kill Them All (extended to OFWGKTADGAFLLBBLSBFBN, meaning Odd Future Wolf Gang Kill Them All Dont Give A Fuck Litter Life Bacon Boys Loiter Squat Butt Fuck Bitch Niggas) normally shortened to Odd Future and abbreviated to OFWGKTA (stylized OFWGK†Δ with an upside down cross), is an American hip hop collective formed in Los Angeles between 2006 and 2007.

The groups founding members include Tyler, The Creator, Hodgy, Left Brain, Casey Veggies, The Super D3Shay, and Jasper Dolphin. Later members include Earl Sweatshirt, Frank Ocean, Domo Genesis, Mike G, and Syd. Outside of music, Odd Future had an Adult Swim sketch-comedy series entitled Loiter Squad. Since 2012, Odd Future has held the annual Camp Flog Gnaw in Los Angeles where members of Odd Future perform alongside a variety of assorting acts in a carnival-esque setting.

description.plain:
The second single released from Odd Future’s succinctly titled OF Tape 2 dropping March 20th. Tyler and Hodgy flex meaninglessly but gloriously over Tyler’s dark, piano-driven instrumental.

We’re not sure why it’s “Ned Flander” (as opposed to the popular Simpsons supporting cast character Ned Flanders) but until we figure out or it’s confirmed for a typo please stop changing it back to the proper spelling.

The video could be interpreted as a prequel to Rella. Hodgy’s balding, mustache-d character is seen swallowing a bottle of pills in the Ned Flander video, possibly hallucinogens. The same unusual characacter is seen at the beginning of the “Rella” video. So, in that case, “Rella” is Hodgy’s hallucination, which explains its left-field premise.

description.plain: This song was an impromptu freestyle session done to the instrumental version of I’ll Whip Ya Head Boy by 50 Cent, from the 2005 Get Rich or Die Tryin' movie soundtrack. This freestyle session was done in Terry Richardson’s New York studio, where the music video for their 2012 song Oldie would later be shot. Odd Future have collaborated with Terry Richardson numerous times throughout their tenure as a group. The video for the freestyle was shot while Odd Future were touring in New York, along with a short mini documentary produced by alternative music news website and Vice subsidiary, Noisey.
